- var encodedImage ="data:image/png;base64,"
doctype html
html(lang='eng')
    head
        meta(http-equiv='Content-Type' content='text/html; charset=UTF-8')
        meta(name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0')
        meta(charset='utf-8')
        base(href='/acidv1')
        title The Archival Acid Test 1.0
        include headerStyle
        script(type='text/javascript' src='arrayBuffer.js')
    body
        h1 The Archival Acid Test
        p.
            This page was setup to test the capabilities and shortcomings of archival web crawlers.
            More information about the rationale and individual tests can be found
            #[a(href="#moreInfo") below].
            For questions/comments contact
            #[a(href="mailto:archiveacidtest@matkelly.com?subject=Archive Acid test comment") Mat Kelly].
        h2 The Tests
        h3 The Basics (5 Tests)
        div#test1
            // Test 1a, Local Image, relative
            img(src="pixel.png" title="test1a")
            // Test 1b, Local Image, absolute
            img(src="http://acid.matkelly.com/pixel.png" title="test1b")
            // Test 1c, Remote Image, absolute
            img(src="http://www.cs.odu.edu/~mkelly/acid/pixel.png" title="test1c")
            // Test 1d, Inline Content, Encoded Image
            img(src={encodedImage} title="test1d")
        h3 Javascript (7 tests)
        div#scriptParent
            // Test 2a, Script, local
            script(type='text/javascript' src='localScript.js' id='localScript')
            // Test 2b, Script, remote
            script(type="text/javascript" src="http://www.cs.odu.edu/~mkelly/acid/externalScript.js" id="externalScript")
            include twoCInline
        h3 HTML5 Features (2 tests)
        div#html5Parent
            include 3aScript
        h2#moreInfo More Information
        h3 The Motivation3
        p The purpose of this web page is to test the capability of web crawlers intended for archiving (e.g., Heritrix) and potentially their corresponding replay systems (e.g., Wayback). 

        h3 Tests' Rationales3
        p Tell an archival crawler to capture this page. Replay the capture in an archival replay system. Any non-blue squares means that some aesthetic or functionality capability of the page on the live web is not being preserved into the archive.

        h4 The Basics
        ul
            li 1a - Local image, relative to the test
            li 1b - Local image, absolute URI
            li 1c - Remote image, absolute
            li 1d - Inline content, encoded image
            li 1e - Scheme-less resource
            li 1f - Hotlinking span(not implemented)

        h4 JavaScript
        ul
            li 2a - Script, local
            li 2b - Script, remote
            li 2c - Script inline, DOM manipulation
            li 2d - Ajax image replacement of content that should be in archive
            li 2e - Ajax requests with content that should be included in the archve, test for false positive (e.g., same origin policy)
            li 2f - Code only served to certain user agents (e.g., mobile) span(not implemented)
            li 2g - Code that manipulates DOM after a certain delay (test the synchronicity of the tools)
            li 2h - spanVacant
            li 2i - Code that loads content only after user interaction (tests for interaction-reliant loading of a resource)

        h4 HTML5 Features
        ul
            li 3a - HTML5 Canvas Drawing
            li 3b - LocalStorage
            li 3c - Exernal Webpage span(not implemented)
            li 3d - XSS Allowed span(not implemented)
            li 3e - XSS Disallowed span(not implemented)
            li 3f - Embedded Objects span(not implemented)

        p#test2iHeightAssurance &nbsp;